&lt;p&gt;Nursing Associate – Endoscopy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Up to 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contract type: Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you always strive to offer excellent patient care?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Then we may have the job for you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has become available for a Nursing Associate to join the Team within the Endoscopy Unit at York.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be be caring for inpatients and outpatients pre, intra and post procedure. You will be assisting with procedures which will include:- Gastroscopy, Colonoscopy, Flexible Sigmoidoscopy, ERCP, PEG, Bowel Cancer Screening, Bronchoscopy and EBUS. Full training will be given no experience necessary.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a robust training package in place for all of our staff as they engage in a wide range of clinical procedures across multiple medical specialties. We are passionate about enabling staff to develop and extend their scope of practice, and keen that all team members are involved in developing the service but also themselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whatever your background, we promise you a warm welcome and all the help and support we can offer to help you become the very best you can be. This includes a first rate induction, access to a range of development programmes and an excellent staff benefits package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of the out of hours on call GI bleed rota. Hours 8am-8pm – 7 day working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It&#39;s not just the area that&#39;s a great draw, as well: as a member of our team, you’ll have access to one of the most generous and comprehensive pension schemes in the UK, a minimum of 27 days annual leave (on top of Bank Holidays) and an award-winning package of staff benefits (see link on the right).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle Robinson - Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;michelle.robinson@york.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01904 726690&lt;/p&gt;
